FBIS4-19913 "drweu078__a94004" FBIS-WEU-94-076-A Daily Report 22 April 1994 ANNEX Inter-European Affairs Germany, Netherlands Establish Military Unit Germany, Netherlands Establish Military Unit AU2104114394 Hamburg DPA in German 0945 GMT 21 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2104114394 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The German-Dutch Corps will be established in The Hague on Friday [22 April] as the first joint military unit of the two countries. Defense Minister Volker Ruehe (Christian Democratic Union) and his Dutch counterpart Relus ter Beek will sign the agreement, the FRG Defense Ministry announced on Thursday [21 April] in Bonn. The corps will probably comprise between 50,000 and 70,000 soldiers. The corps will be commanded by a joint corps staff in Muenster. Full combat readiness is to be reached in 1995. The first commander will be Dutch Major General Ruurd Reitsma. The first such unit to be established was the German-French corps, which was later supplemented by Belgian units.
